==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heathenism
<hw>Hea"then*ism</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The religious system or rites of a heathen nation; idolatry;
paganism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The manners or morals usually prevalent in a heathen
country; ignorance; rudeness; barbarism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heathenize</ent>⟦br⟧
